cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.DS 

The paper deals with optimization algorithms and proposes a deep learning architecture based on convolutional neural network for algorithm selection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also proposes a novel method to extract landscape information from optimization problems and save it as 2-D images, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which could also be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
